import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    box_plot = data.boxplot(column='rate', by='region')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of obesity rates across different regions?")
    plt.suptitle("")
    plt.xlabel("Region")
    plt.ylabel("Obesity Rate")
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        box_plot.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_obesity_rate = data.groupby('state')['rate'].mean()
    avg_obesity_rate.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average obesity rate in each state?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Obesity Rates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of obesity rates?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
